===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|i}} – The top component is [[𠁳]], a pot full of plants [[丰]] (abundance, plenty). The bottom component is {{zh-l|*豆}}, which is another pot.

Unrelated to [[豊]], in which two strings of jade pieces [[玨]] are present. The top component of 豐 is unrelated to [[山]].

===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} compares a {{cog|my||tr=pruiŋᴮ|t=full, abundant}}, which would be written in Burmese script as {{m|my||ပြိုင်း}}; however, no such word with that spelling shows up in the MED (Myanmar English Dictionary). It appears more likely that the item Schuessler wishes to compare is {{m|my|ပြည့်|t=to be full}} or  {{m|my|ဖြိုင်ဖြိုင်|t=plentifully, abundantly}}

